13
00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:43.730
Measure his woe the lengthand breadth of mine

14
00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:46.030
And let it answer everystrain for strain,

15
00:00:46.030 --> 00:00:48.100
As thus for thus andsuch a grief for such,

16
00:00:48.100 --> 00:00:50.870
In every lineament,branch, shape, and form:

17
00:00:50.870 --> 00:00:54.470
If such a one will smileand stroke his beard,

18
00:00:54.470 --> 00:01:01.570
bring him yet to me, And I ofhim will gather patience.

19
00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:04.970
But there is no suchman: for, brother,

20
00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:07.730
men Can counsel and speakcomfort to that grief

21
